==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thomsonite
<hw>Thom"son*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From R. D.
<etsep>Thomson</etsep>, of Glasgow.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
zeolitic mineral, occurring generally in masses of a radiated structure.
It is a hydrous silicate of aluminia, lime, and soda. Called also
<altname>mesole</altname>, and <altname>comptonite</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thomson process</ent>⟦br⟧
